You are here:

Use a pie chart when you have multiple groupings and want to show the proportion of a single value for each grouping against the total.

REQUIRED EDITIONS
Available in: Salesforce Classic (not available in all orgs)
Available in: Group, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

For example, to see the breakdown of your case queue by case status in a report, set record count for Values and status for Wedges. The chart displays a circle made up of wedges, each wedge representing the cases in a case status. Wedge size is proportional to the numbers of cases.

Pie charts are not ideal for comparing values that are close together or numerous small values.

Select Show Labels, Show Values, or Show Wedge % to include that information on the chart. (Only available with Chart Analytics 2.0.)
